# Upload Your First Android App on Play Store (Step-by-Step):

![android-app-on-google-play-512](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/27420533/72202676-38a10880-345a-11ea-8834-50e32c03f2f3.png)


This post is for anyone thinking of putting an App or game on the Play Store.</br>
So just follow all the steps to quickly get the App online and ready to be installed on the Play Store.

## 1.Create Your Android App

The first thing to do when you want to have your own application or game online is to create the app and have the application ready to be published.</br> 
You should use the colors, themes, graphics and icons that you like the most and that match well with the application and its purpose.

## 2.Make its Signed Apk

To generate keystores for signing Android apps go to Android Studio (Build > Generate Signed Bundle/Apk).

![KZW3K2vS4G](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/27420533/72202703-99c8dc00-345a-11ea-8004-5e5bf93256f6.png)

This screen will pop-up and you need to chose (APK) then click next.


![rZKR1cgQFE](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/27420533/72202730-c7158a00-345a-11ea-814f-198961f079ff.png)

A debug keystore which is used to sign an Android App during development needs a specific alias and password combination as dictated
by Google.
So you need to give your project a path for your app a, password and an alias.


## 3.Login to your Gmail Account and visit this link:
https://play.google.com/apps/publish/

![1SOjy5FNUy](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/27420533/72202915-e0b7d100-345c-11ea-9ea3-4a9b59f4eecc.png)

## 4.Create your developer Account in Google 

![QSPJnkS7X2](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/27420533/72202947-3d1af080-345d-11ea-943a-533b1998efa5.png)

Note: You will be charged a one-time fee of $25.
After you have been paid this amount you can start uploading your first App.

## 5.Fields needed in App Listing:
- Title
- Short description
- Full description
- App Screenshots
- Icon
- Feature graphic
- App Type
- Category
- Content Rating
- Developer Email
- Privacy Policy URL

After filling all the data correctly the App will be saved as a draft until Google authorizes the exit of the application to the platform.












